I&#39;ve never posted an EVP but I do like to read about everyone else. Am I OK?

On Fri, May 28, 2010 at 10:25 AM, Rj &lt;rasterer@...&gt; wrote:

&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Same here - I have said  (several  times before) that since I have no
&gt; results I consider can only be explained paranormally, I have not posted
&gt; them.  As soon as I  get those, I will post them.  But I don&#39;t see the point
&gt; of me just posting stuff to say &#39;me too!&#39;, or to follow the crowd, or to try
&gt; to fit in.  I am not disparaging those who have those results, and do post
&gt; them.  And since this is a discussion,group, it seems we should be able to
&gt; discuss them, and question, and make suggestions.
&gt;
&gt; Civilly.
&gt;
&gt; Also, Misty, there is more to &#39;research&#39; than everybody doing and saying
&gt; the same thing.  Even in what might seem a well-scoped area of study, people
&gt; can be at different levels of knowledge, or interest, or focus.  Some people
&gt; here are interested mostly in the hardware.  Some have no interest or talent
&gt; there, and focus on using the technology.  Some stand back some, looking at
&gt; process, controls, quality assurance.  Some may just be interested in the
&gt; psychic or paranormal components.  Some may be more interested in the &quot;Is
&gt; there anything there&quot; question.  Some, &quot;I know something&#39;s there, but what
&gt; is it?&quot;.  Some &quot;I know there are ghosts there, what do they want?&quot;.  Some,
&gt; &quot;I know what they want, how can I help?&quot;.  And so on.
&gt;
&gt; One person giving their perspective, in a different focus, or a different
&gt; opinion, is not, &quot;crap&quot;, or &quot;wasting time&quot;.   It should be seen as healthy,
&gt; helping a science stretch and check, redirect or confirm,  grow and
&gt; explore.  To swat that down is a source of the negativity.  And if you are
&gt; concerned about negative comments, go back and read the threads, and see who
&gt; is actually making the insults.
&gt;
&gt; But, to make what I consider a positive suggestion, I would suggest people
&gt; stop insulting others with different opinions, and allow civil discussion,
&gt; and consider that none of us knows it all, and can still learn things from
&gt; others.  In fact, I hope that is the real purpose of the group.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
